 the team for the remainder of middle school in hopes to earn respect and get that girlfriend I always wished for, but I got neither. (This was before I knew how getting a girlfriend actually works) One day 8th grade in early 2014, after watching youtubers become famous, I made that my dream, to become a popular gaming YouTuber, something I put my heart into. I worked hard trying to make content, eventually one of the football players caught me looking at my channel on my phone, and told everyone in the school about it. I was made fun of for the rest of the year about it. And that was the day I got depressed. My dreams were absolutely crushed, demolished, burned into smithereens, just like that. I was mortified, and was bullied for a super long time which made things even worse. If I wasn’t a loser back then, then I certainly was one that day. Late 2014 a freshman and all the way to 2018 as a senior, I had no one to talk to but 4 people who actually took the time to get to know me unlike everyone else who assumes I’m the weirdo. A lot happened though in those 4 years, disappointed people I looked up to, was still picked on, let down the band directors who had faith in me, got screwed over by the school district messing up my classes, 3 heartbreaks, it was rough. Even at my job I don’t say anything cause everyone there is super toxic.( i work at a car shop) I can’t trust anyone, I never talk unless I absolutely have to, and I bottle up my sadness and anger, and put on a mask to pretend I’m fine. I almost got myself into a food disorder. We have this thing where someone stands outside and put air in peoples tires for free. Summer of 2019 I did that for 6 hours straight, 6 days a week, in the burning sun with no shade. I had the thought by not moving around much I would gain weight so I would only eat as little as 200 calories. Until after 2 weeks I got tired of the pain and forced myself to eat more, then was aware of what was happening. It was horrible on my knees, had my knees wrapped and in a brace for 2 months cause the pain of getting up and down repeatedly for 6 hours a day was brutal. I was basically the guy who did the work that no one else did. I never felt so useless in my life, I hated myself so much too, I told myself I wasn’t good enough and I will never be, and that I wasn’t worth it and I should take my own life. Eventually I got out of that mindset after I took matters into my own hands and threatened to call HR about it. They finally put me in a better position. But my depression, anxiety, and self hatred got worse and worse, and still is to this day but I’m still learning to control it. How I realized I was depressed? So keep in mind I didn’t have much people to talk to, and still don’t. Sometimes people come to me when they need someone, but I can’t go to them because “I need to man up” “I got to get over it” etc. Like damn, I didn’t tell you guys that, why do you need to say that to me? Anyways because I can’t talk to literally anyone about stuff, I have to be the doctor, AND the patient to help myself. One day in high school after I accepted the fact I’ll be alone for the rest of my life, I realized something was off, that I wasn’t as calm, quiet as I used to be. I had my parents take me to a therapist and I was diagnosed with depression, anxiety, severe social anxiety and self hatred (low self esteem). Medications haven’t helped at all despite having maximum dosage, so I’ve had to teach myself how to control my emotions, learn to bottle everything up, make myself away that suicide shouldn’t be my death. But my mind was still getting toxic one day I shut myself off to everyone. That lasted for a year until I recovered from that.I admit I’m not in my best mindset, I’m still trying to recover, again I have to doctor myself, but hey, at least I’m trying. The good thing is I’m making little progress. I am learning healthier ways to control my emotions and healthier habits instead of bottling things up making everything a loving nightmare. I can say I am Better than I was last year, it’s not easy doctoring myself, but I hope I’ll get though it all.Thanks
