akaleelei [info] I got a dog after I was diagnosed with depression to be an emotional support animal. At first I got him to just have companionship and to force me to go on walks and just that definitely helped. Having him gave me a purpose in life. After I was diagnosed with anxiety too I started looking into psychological service dogs and tried training him to help with my social anxiety. In my research I learned that dogs can be trained to do a ton of helpful things for people with mental illness. Like helping to remind you to take your meds, getting help for you, disrupting panic attacks etc. I would like to get him professionally trained now to help me. But even without the training having a dog has been a great experience even though he's a lot of work. Do your research before you get a dog so you know what you're getting into and see if it's a good choice for your situation.
