sist that their diagnosis (if they have one) is their diagnosis if they start showing signs of something else as they get older. If they feel like they need to get screened for something else, whether it be Bipolar Disorder, Anorexia, BPD, DID, anything they think or you think they might be struggling with, please get them screened. I attempted suicide 3 times by the time I was 16 and nearly died after overdosing on Tylenol because no one listened to me. Please please listen to your kids. And if you are an adult who is struggling, please don’t hesitate to get a proper diagnosis and get help. It’s not a bad thing. My therapist is like my best friend and she has helped me immensely and I’m hoping to bring up the idea to get screened for either Bipolar or BPD soon.
