 way. They've never been through something like this. Just seek out help from another individual and don't lose hope. You can always DM me when you feel like you hit the bottom. I'm not a professional of course, but it's nice to have people to talk to sometimes. &#x200B;&#x200B;
petulafaerie [info] I had known there was something "wrong" with me for a long time before I received any official diagnosis, but had not given the "wrongness" a specific label before I was diagnosed with depression in my early teens.Around 10 years later I finally sought professional help of my own accord because I felt like I was getting worse (I didn't like the woman who diagnosed me for several reasons and had never had any therapy until this point in my life).  When I did I was diagnosed with depression, general anxiety and social anxiety.  I guess while I had never given myself a specific medical diagnosis, I had always known there was something about me that was different to "normal" "healthy" people.  So I think trust yourself, if you know something is wrong with you then there very well could be, but go and speak to a professional to understand what that wrongness is and let them diagnose you correctly.  
