LilyofManyVallies [info] I was first depressed at 12. It started off with existential stuff- you know, kids finding out that life is hard and that- it ends and we dont understand the reason for anything. That everyone goes through life alone and scared. I couldnt stop THINKING. And eventually I became suicidal. I had a plan, but I kept it all togethet and eventually the episode passed.I didnt have another until I was 15. It wasnt as bad, but its also when the hallucinations started. They were really rare at first, once every 4-6 months or so. The first one was a cat. I was on vacation with my family, I had just taken some cold medication or something (I forget what) and I woke up to get some water and there was this black cat in the room with me. I spent like an hour searching the condo for the cat, and nothing. I figured it was the drugs and just went back to bed. I didnt have another for about the 4-6 months and because they were so rare I just tried to dismiss them. Its my usual response to life- denial until I cant any longer. I had the occasional episode of hypomania (I technically have schizoaffective disorder) which caused me problems when I was younger with impusivity. But also, I spent my senior year of high school on and off hypomanic and it was the only year I made straight As. The lowest grade I had was a 99.7% because it was the first time in a long time that I felt that I had consistent energy. I went to college the next year. My freahman year was stressful but I kept it together. My sophomore year was when things got really bad. I started getting really depressed again. It got to the point where I almost completely stopped going to classes. I basically stopped doing anything but laying in bed, in pain, wishing I were dead. It then got to the point where I realized that- there were only two options, either I kill myself or I get help. I decided to get help. I went to my schools counseling center and started seeing a counselor and a psychiatrist. I was diagnosed with depression. They put me on antidepressants. I had hope for the antidepressants, I really did. I took them faithfully. I thought that I finally had something that would make me feel good about life again. But things just got worse.I started getting really paranoid. I thougjt people were planning on hurting me. I couldnt leave my dorm without having panic attacks, because I would see people laughing to each other and I thought they were laughing because they had finally figured out how to kill me. The hallucinations revved up. I stopped sleeping too because the hallucinations were worse at night and I felt that staying up was safer. I was hearing voices around me saying that I was evil and deserved to die. I started thinking that there was some evil inside me, and that I had to cut it out with knives. That if I could just bleed the rot out of me than anything would be fine. So I started self harming.Eventually I was put on a low dose antipsychotic which- immediatey started helping. I started leaving my dorm. The voices started going away and the paranoia decreased. The thought that people wanted to hurt me just stopped happening. I started going to class and I started doing well. My psychiatrist started completely phasing out my antidepressant with an increased dose of the antipsychotic and I eventually started feeling like I had my life back. My diagnosis was changed to bipolar NOS and it was assumed that the psychosis was from the antidepressant. Things were good for about a year and a half. I still had the very occasional hallucination and I had side effects from the medication- but for the most part, I got by. I was still having mood episodes, but they were much more manageable. I had help and it was great.But then a year and a half ago things started getting worse. I was having hallucinations more and more. Some nights I was having such intense ones that- I stopped sleeping again. Eventually I started hearing voices telling me that the meds were bad. God talked to me and told me to stop taking tjem, that I only needed to believe in him and that he would provide for me. I wanted to believe it so badly, I hated that I was still getting hallucinations AND had to take this medication that made me feel a little dull. I wanted to believe rhat nothing was wrong with me and that- all my issues from before were sort of- that the treatment that I already done had cured them.I started getting really sick really quickly after stopping my antipsychotic. As I said, I stopped sleeping mostly. I slept as little as possible. The hallucinations got so much worse. I stopped speaking too because whenever Id open my mouth my pitch would be off and I just- my words felt mixed up and I was afraid if I scared someone they would send me to a hospital. I wanted this all to work out and I knew it wouldnt if someone sent me away. I stopped going out again anf I started getting really paranoid. I stopped eating, bathing, and stopped doing homework. I almost completely cut myself off from people. I kept a journal back then (which I deleted a few months ago) and my words were... scary. They were a whole bunch of basically nonsense about jesus and demons and poison and WHY WAS EVERYONE OUT TO GET ME. And it was all jumbled and I kept saying how scared I was and why everything couldnt just leave me alone. Everything was disjointed and lots of it was hard to make sense of. But mostly it was a lot of fear and me asking why it wouldnt stop. I thought that god was talking to me in various forms of media and- it was all so confusing.I had an appointment where I aaw my therapist and she was super scared. She basically... she had no idea what to do. She kept asking if I wanted her to call someone. Begged me to go to the ER. And when I said I wouldnt she basically forced me to let her talk to my psychiatrist. She called my psychiatrist and I had an appointment with her a few days later.I went there and she basically said I was in HORRIBLE shape and that she really didnt want me to have to go to the hospital because- somehow I was still passing my classes and I had made it- well. I hadnt told her that I was a danger to myseld (I dont think- I think I tried to make aure I didnt, because I just was really scared about being hospitalized- but I dont remember for sure because its all a little blurry). She gave me a choice of going to the hospital or making several close appointments in a row with both her and my therapist and restarting my medication.I did the second thing. I restarted it. It was really really hard for me to do but I didnt want to go to the hospital and I knew that- if I didnt start it again there was a high likelihood Id be involuntarily committed... because that had been floated. She had said she didnt want to do that if she didnt 100% have to because of my situation and because its also trauamatic. So, after spending a couple of days freaking out every time I HAD to take it, and spending a couple of days throwing it up because I thought it was poison and I was just sooo confused- well. Eventually I started it again. My symtoms started calming down again. I started seeing a new therapist because mt other therapist said that she felt I needed more care than she could provide, and things were ok for a while.I was diagnosed with schizoaffectice bipolar type at this pointBut I dont like taking it. I didnt like taking it. I didnt like feeling trapped in sickness. I wanted to prove to myself that I was ok.So a few months ago I stopped it again. Things were fine for a while. I was watched closely by my psychologist and while- she HATED that I was doing this AGAIN... she said shed be there with me during it.Until things got bad again. I started thinking that people were trying to hurt me again. I thought that my body was rotten and that the demon was marking me to make me some sort of conduit between the spiritual world and the real world. I thought I had a special mission and that no one could understand and that the world was against me.So. I let a little of this slip. And though I was trying to keep it secret because I didnt think anyone would understand... she got it out of me. And she called mt psychitrist again.Rinse and repeat of the time before, though this time I wasnt as far gone. I was warnes that I needed to STOP doing this- because I was harming my brain... and so... yeah.I stayed on those meds for like, 3 months? Until I had to move home. I moved home at the start of this semester and they keep wanting to cut all my meds down. Its been super frustrating and I am scared of what will happen. But I told my last psychiatrist when I left that I would try to listen to my psychiatrists in the future and NOT mess with my medication on my own. So I am trying to lisren because that psychologisr I was seeing was REALLY GOOD and I felt like she really did want to help me. But its been hard because I dont feel like they really... know me or my situation. I feel like they are experimenting on me. Im on 1/4 of the medication I was on a few months ago and its been progressively harder to function consistently. I see a new psychiatrist in december that I saw over the summer a few years ago. I trust her more than I do the people I just saw. So I just have to make it until the middle of next month and then maybe, maybe things can be okSorry this is so long. Just thought Id get my story out there because thats probably the most comprehensive way to answer all those questionsOh and about your other questions- I have only started being more open about my diagnosis- but I still only tell it on a I feel- would be good for this person to know basis. I have a hard time accepting my diagnosis and the need for treatment. It definitely sometimes gets in the way of school- but I try not to let it. And most of all, I am scared but still hopeful
