s of joy then I don't even feel like I "deserve" it because I have become so used to this depressive state... It really sucks struggling to just do basic tasks like waking up, getting out of bed, brushing your teeth, keeping a routine, eating food.. let alone memorizing useless information in school and having to socially interact with people with a smile on your face just so you get money to live.. especially when it's an invisible disability. I was able to do that stuff with a "structure" that was enforced upon me but I never realized all these years just how much extra effort I had to put into doing things than the average neurotypical person... just to achieve mediocre results.
